      "airport": "Naples International Airport (NAP)",
      "to_city": "Curreri bus from Naples airport to Sorrento (€10, 70min) then SITA bus along the coast. Car service (€100+, 90min). Ferry from Naples to Positano/Amalfi (€25, 80min) - seasonal",
      "best_time": "May-June or September. July-August is a festival of crowds. October can be wet but is peaceful",
      "eating": [
        "Limoncello was invented on Amalfi - it's a digestif, not a cocktail. Drink it after dinner, ice cold",
        "Scialatielli ai frutti di mare is the local pasta - thick ribbons with seafood",
        "Delizia al limone is a lemon dessert from Amalfi - light, sweet, perfect",
        "Positano restaurant prices are 30% higher than Amalfi town for the same quality"
      ],
      "safety": [
        "The bus is safe but pickpocketing happens on crowded summer buses",
        "Steps everywhere - good shoes are non-negotiable",
        "Emergency: 112 (EU-wide). Coast Guard for boat emergencies: 1530"
      ],
      "local_tips": [
        "Book restaurants in Positano weeks ahead in summer - the good ones fill up instantly",
        "The Path of the Gods is free and the most beautiful thing you can do here",
        "Take the ferry between towns, not the bus - it's faster, cooler, and the views are better",
        "Buy limoncello from a family producer, not a souvenir shop - ask at your hotel"
      ]
